This hierarchy is the distribution for lcc, the retargetable compiler
for ANSI C described in the book `A Retargetable C Compiler: Design and
Implementation' (Addison-Wesley, 1995, ISBN 0-8053-1670-1).

LOG describes the changes since the last release.

CPYRIGHT describes the conditions under you can use, copy, modify, and
distribute lcc or works derived from lcc.

doc/install.html is an HTML file that gives a complete description of
the distribution and installation instructions.

NB: The distribution hierarchy and the installation procedures have
changed with this release; see doc/install.html or visit
http://www.cs.princeton.edu/software/lcc/pkg/install.html.

The DOS executable files are not included in this distribution.
They are available in the 3.5 distribution at
http://www.cs.princeton.edu/software/lcc/old/

